{{Infobox magazine | logo = | logo_size = <!-- default is 180px --> | image_file = <!-- cover.jpg (omit the "file:" prefix) --> | image_size = <!-- default is 180px --> | image_alt = | image_caption = | editor = Thomas R. Kellaway | editor_title = <!-- up to |editor_title5= --> | previous_editor = | staff_writer = | photographer = | category = Art magazine | frequency = Bimonthly | format = | circulation = | publisher = | paid_circulation = | unpaid_circulation = | circulation_year = | total_circulation = | founder = Thomas R. Kellaway | founded = | firstdate = {{Start date|1973|09}} | finaldate = | finalnumber = | company = | country = United States | based = [[Stratham, New Hampshire]] | language = English | website = {{URL|http://amartrevsecure.com}} | issn = 0092-1327 | oclc = }} '''''American Art Review''''' is an [[art magazine]] founded and edited by [[Thomas R. Kellaway]] who published the magazine from September 1973 until November 1978. In the summer of 1992 he revived the magazine, which is published to this day.<ref>[http://www.tfaoi.com/aa/4aa/4aa348.htm TFAO]</ref> It is published on a bimonthly basis and was headquartered in [[Shawnee Mission, Kansas]].<ref>{{cite book|author=David J. Maloney Jr.|title=Maloney's Antiques and Collectibles Resource Directory|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=KwRr8MqB7r4C&pg=PT74|accessdate=5 February 2017|date=January 2003|publisher=Krause Publications|isbn=0-87349-732-5|page=74}}</ref> The magazine is based in [[Stratham, New Hampshire]].<ref>{{cite web|title=American Art Review|url=https://bizstanding.com/directory/NH/AM/59/|work=Business Directory|accessdate=5 February 2017}}</ref>
''American Art Review'' concentrates on [[Visual art of the United States|American art]] from the colonial era until the early 1970s. It focuses especially on exhibitions of figurative art in regional museums. The content is generally divided between scholarly articles on artists and advertisements from galleries. {{clear}}
