'''Sally Gary''' (born September 19, 1961) is a speaker and author on the [[Christian]] approach to [[homosexuality]].<ref>{{cite news|last=Lewis|first=Christianna|title=Conference to address same-sex attraction|url=http://www.acuoptimist.com/2009/09/conference-to-address-same-sex-attraction/|accessdate=3 June 2013|newspaper=The Optimist|date=22 September 2009|deadurl=yes|archiveurl=https://archive.is/20130628091440/http://www.acuoptimist.com/2009/09/conference-to-address-same-sex-attraction/|archivedate=28 June 2013|df=}}</ref>
==Life== Gary was born in [[Wichita Falls, Texas]]. She grew up going to Tenth and Broad Church of Christ in Wichita Falls.<ref>Ross Jr., Bobby, (September 2013), [http://www.christianchronicle.org/article2160045~Homosexuality_and_the_church Homosexuality and the church]. The Christian Chronicle. Retrieved 29 July 2013.</ref> She attended [[Abilene Christian University]] and has a law degree from [[Texas Tech University]]. In 2006, Gary founded [http://centerpeace.net/ CenterPeace], a nonprofit ministry that creates safe spaces for Christians to talk about homosexuality.<ref>{{cite news|last=Kieke|first=Carl|title=Local conference deals with same-sex relationships|url=http://www.reporternews.com/news/2009/sep/25/hed-hed-hedp/?print=1|accessdate=3 June 2013|newspaper=Abilene Reporter News|date=25 September 2009}}</ref> Gary also taught at [[Abilene Christian University]] in the department of [[communication]] from 2001 to 2011.<ref>{{cite news|last=Tryggestad|first=Erik|title=Same-sex attraction: Cutting through the shame, secrecy|url=http://www.christianchronicle.org/article2082544~Same-sex_attraction%3A_Cutting_through_the_shame,_secrecy|accessdate=3 June 2013|newspaper=The Christian Chronicle|date=September 2006}}</ref> In 2013 Gary authored ''Loves God, Likes Girls'', a memoir telling the story of her own journey experiencing [[homosexuality]].<ref>{{cite news|last=Menzie|first=Nicole|title='Loves God, Likes Girls' Author Talks Myths Christians Believe About Same-Sex Attraction|url=http://www.christianpost.com/news/loves-god-likes-girls-author-talks-myths-christians-believe-about-same-sex-attraction-98978/#vR9FxigoU3OZWB3Z.99|accessdate=16 July 2013|newspaper=The Christian Post|date=12 July 2013}}</ref>
==Education== *B.S.Ed [[Abilene Christian University]] (1983) *M.A. [[Abilene Christian University]] (1985) *J.D. [[Texas Tech University]] (1998)
==Publications== *''Loves God, Likes Girls: A Memoir'', [[Abilene, Texas]]: [[Leafwood Publishers]], 2013. {{ISBN|978-0-89112-359-0}}.
